description:
Previously published in three installments, the entire run of comic master Osamu Tezuka's enduring classic is herewith available in one volume at a new affordable price. The lauded adventures of a young swordsman and his rogue sidekick that also inspired the cult video game Blood Will Tell have never been as accessible.

A samurai lord has bartered away his newborn son's organs to forty-eight demons in exchange for dominance on the battlefield. Yet, the abandoned infant survives thanks to a medicine man who equips him with primitive prosthetics - lethal ones with which the wronged son will use to hunt down the multitude of demons to reclaim his body one piece at a time, before confronting his father. On his journeys the young hero encounters an orphan who claims to be the greatest thief in Japan.

Like an unforgettable road movie, Dororo reaches deeper than its swashbuckling surface and offers a thoughtful allegory of becoming what one is, for nobody, in born whole.
name: GN

description:
The second chapter of this fantastic adventure is here!

ARHIAN goes on a dangerous mission to rescue Viceroy’s daughter, GINA and find herself entering THALDOON, the City of Horrors!

Don’t wait to check this exhilarating second part of this fantastic adventure that will change ARHIAN’s life forever!

Note: The digital edition (5/25/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Don’t wait to check out this explosive second chapter of ASTRIA’s saga! Deeper and deeper into a path of self-destruction and revenge, ASTRIA is unable to distinguish innocents from those who are guilty for the destruction of her family.

…Or maybe they are not really innocent victims! Are they?

You tell us!

Note: The digital edition (5/25/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Summer’s getaway plan spreads out before her like an endless horizon. It might seem foolish to burn all your bridges before you've left an island but Summer can always make a raft out of the dead bodies left in her wake. From Sami Kivelä [artist on Zenescope’s HIT LIST] and Ryan K Lindsay [the writer of Dark Horse’s NEGATIVE SPACE] comes this year’s pulpiest crime tale.

description:
They were 6, they eventually end to 4, and Faith is not done with them

Spanich Conquistador Cortés hires Hernando Del Royo to rally Jungle tribes against Aztec Emperor Moctezuma Realm. A new war is coming, bloody, brutal, savage. The second cycle of the acclaimed Conquistador series goes wilds and doesn't really holds its breath! The dark and fascinating power of Aztec wizards will strike again and life will be changed forever.
name: Book 4

description: Batwoman returns to Berlin to aid Catwoman. There, Batwoman is unexpectedly reunited with her ex-lover, Renee Montoya, and we get a glimpse of their romantic and complicated past.
name: Ghost Stories Part 3 of 3

description:
The Terror that Flaps in the Night is back in the second installment of the all-new ongoing comic series! Megavolt and Negaduck have unleashed the collective might of the inmates at the St. Canard Prison for the Criminally Conniving, and Darkwing is trapped inside alone - or is he? And who's really behind all this tomfoolery? The comeback of the century continues!

Note: Liquidator, Megavolt and Negaduck have a one-page profile at the end of this issue.
name: Orange Is the New Purple Part II

description: Reunited but not resolved, Charli and Lucy go on the offensive versus threats both human and fantastical as they close-in on their prime suspect.

Streets flow with rivers of fire and skies are filled with demons. In this, the final issue in the second arc of John Carpenter's Asylum, God is dead. The Anti-Christ is near, and Beckett, the fallen angel, is humanity's last hope.

AGP's explosively violent original series continues! While Timothy Choir is only narrowly avoiding violent death from his opponents, regulators of the Killbox demonstrate their ruthlessness by recruiting several crime organizations and obliterating the one that refuses to cooperate. Not quite sure what he's up against, Timothy breaks taboo and teams up with fellow contestant Emi Nari-a move that will endanger both of their lives.

Angel's big date with Lisa turns into more of an adventure than he anticipated when a kidnapping plot is foiled by a giant were-tiger… who turns out to be his chauffer! Not only does this discovery turn his world upside down, but he also learns some very troubling information about his father... and a Fate that has been sealed for him since birth!

One of the French top-key novel amazingly adapted into a furious and overwhelming comics

We all know the story: in the Parisian Middle Age, Esmeralda, Gypsy Beauty, dances in front of Notre Dame Cathedral. She involuntary seduces Archdeacon Frollo who tries to catch her with the help of the Hunchback Quasimodo. But Captain Phoebus, true love of Esmeralda, helps her to escape. Robin Recht and Jean Bastide propose a bewitching tale in two parts, with very modern art, fury, passion and despair. Notre Dame is a masterpiece which benefits here of the combined talent of two young but yet major French comics artists.
name: Destiny

description:
For Freedom, Brotherhood and Honor.

The Riff rised and all Marocco threatens to follow... Calixte, recently converted to Islam, became a War Dog and took the name of "Khalil al Islami". Léon on his side has to choose between fortune and brotherhood. He eventually joins his force to his close friend and to the rebels. Faces to them stand two colonial armies, the French and the Spanish, partners in defense of their own Empire. The Republic of the Rif has no long to live – even if the Death is behind the door, victory is not requested anymore to build Legends...
name: Khalil

description: Helix warrior Fareeha Amari—code name PHARAH—leads her squad to neutralize a dangerous artificial intelligence that has taken over omnic soldiers, intent on wreaking havoc in Egypt—and in the process, she learns a vital lesson about leadership and character.
name: Pharah: Mission Statement

description: So... Tell me about love. Today is Chris and Laura's one year anniversary. I can't imagine this time last year Chris was thinking, "you know what, a year from now, I bet my relationship with Laura will have completely fallen apart, I'll be harboring a zombie girl named Jessica in a storage locker, occasionally murdering innocent folks to feed her, and I'll have no exit strategy from this living nightmare that has consumed my every waking minute." And yet... here we are. True love is dead in 451's Self Storage #5.
